The Federal Government has suspended, indefinitely, the operations of the microblogging and social networking service, Twitter, in Nigeria. Minister of Information and Culture, Lai Mohammed, announced the suspension in a statement signed his  Special Assistant Segun Aseyemi citing the persistent use of the platform for activities that are capable of undermining Nigeriaâ€™s corporate existence. The Minister said the Federal Government has also directed the National Broadcasting Commission (NBC) to immediately commence the process of licensing all OTT and social media operations in Nigeria.